    <title>EDITING: Copy and Paste for Images / Shapes Wonky in Writer</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">1 In Writer, Insert Shape or Image</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">2 While Shape/Image is still highlighted, CTRL+X then CTRL+V</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Expected Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">1 A copy of your Shape/Image is placed on top of or below and to the right of your original Shape/Image.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">2 The copied object should be selected.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Actual Results:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">1 Nothing</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Both Calc and Impress, work as expected.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">I also tested Corel WordPerfect, MS Word, and Kingsoft Writer.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">They also all behaved as expected.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
